ill offer incredible advantages to businesses such as the following:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li><strong>The offer better rates at lower fees<\/strong><\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Therefore, the likelihood of getting dinged with various fees for any online financial transaction, including maintenance fees, paying by debit cards or check or making direct deposits. Furthermore, you are less likely to find a online bank that comes with services fees or minimum balance.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are incredible benefits of online banking for business because these online financial institutions don\u2019t have incur any overhead costs and do not have significant infrastructure. Therefore, they find themselves offering higher annual percentage yields (APYs) or interest rates on savings. Some can even offer up to 2% more than those offered at traditional banks.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"2\"><li><strong>Offer better online experience to customers<\/strong><\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Inasmuch as many brick-and-mortar banks are continuously trying to invest heavily on improving their online presence to ensure that they attend to their online customers better, online banks are seeming taking the lead on this one because they still retain their competitive edge.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is according to a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bain.com\/about\/media-center\/press-releases\/2018\/loyalty-in-banking\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">2018 report<\/a> from a survey carried out by Bain and Company, which discovered that conventional banks lagged behind when it comes to better online experiences than online banking, especially on the aspects that mattered the most. Some of these areas were the simplicity in transactions, speed and quality of the banking experiences.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"3\"><li><strong>Come with superior site interfaces<\/strong><\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Many online banks feature sophisticated and superior user interfaces with multiple fantastic features like faster response time. Some of them even come with easy-to-use mobile apps that prove to be very convenient for customers while ensuring that there is streamlined account management at the touch of a screen.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>For traditional banks, offering superior website interfaces often come as afterthoughts, which means that they just rush through them. However, there are some big names in the industry that are doing their best to retool their internet banking systems to compete with the online-only counterparts.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"4\"><li><strong>It\u2019s quick and easy to open an account<\/strong><\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Since these banks are entirely online, you essentially can do practically everything online, including setting up your account. You will not be restricted by the physical banking hours. This means that you can choose to open your account on a Sunday night after dessert without any restrictions. Therefore, you save a lot of time escaping traffic and queuing at the local branch. It is essentially banking at your fingertips.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"400\" src=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/high-yield-savings-business-banking-1.jpg\" alt=\"online banking\" class=\"wp-image-588\" srcset=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/high-yield-savings-business-banking-1.jpg 800w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/high-yield-savings-business-banking-1-300x150.jpg 300w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/high-yield-savings-business-banking-1-768x384.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Cons of online banking you should know<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>There are also some share of disadvantages with using online banking. They include:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 <strong>Absence of personal relationships:<\/strong> A conventional bank lets you interact with its staff on a personal level. Such personal relationships could be advantageous, especially when it comes to additional financial services. Also, you can easily engage with a manager to tailor some terms to suit your business needs.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 <strong>There is less flexibility with the transactions: <\/strong>In case of any issues with any transactions, it is easier to sort it out with an in-person staffer than an online agent. Therefore, you may need to read the fine print of the bank\u2019s policy on some of these issues before you proceed to engaging them for their services.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022<strong> Most of them don\u2019t own ATMs: <\/strong>Most of the online banks don\u2019t have their own banking machines. As such, they have to rely on customers having to use multiple ATM networks. Inasmuch as they offer access to ATMs around the world, you may have to first research if the work with the ATMs around your workplace or where you live. At the same time, you should ensure that you assess the fees for using some of these machines because some ATMs could be quite expensive for some online banking platforms.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 <strong>Limited services<\/strong>: In some few instances, you might encounter online banks that are limited in services as compared to traditional bank, including brokerage or insurance accounts. In some cases, loyal customers in traditional banks enjoy special services such as investment advice or preferred rates at no extra charge.<br>Conclusion<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Therefore, what is online banking? Essentially, it is a financial institution working exclusively or mostly online and they come with a number of pros and con. As seen above, there are some pretty cool advantages of e banking but also there are some bad things about online banking depending on the types of online banking chosen. For you to fully enjoy the benefits of online banking and advantages of online banking over traditional banking, ensure that you read and understand the fine print.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Introduction As you think about where to bank, you should first start thinking about the kind of financial institution in the payments industry you need. This trickles down to choosing between the conventional brick-and-mortar banks the their online counterparts. What will mostly guide your decision are the advantages and disadvantages of online banking over the [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":603,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[16],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/450"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/2"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=450"}],"version-history":[{"count":2,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/450\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":590,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/450\/revisions\/590"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/603"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=450"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=450"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=450"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}